# Set user as verified automatically · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #3786
created: 2023-11-19, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/3786)

The default validation error message is kindof confusing but regular users are not allowed to change their `verified` status directly.
It's value will change to `true` once the user verify their email OR when an admin update it manually.
...
Alternatively, if you really want to set the value to `true` by default, you can register a before create hook.
Here is an example using the JS pb_hooks:
```
// pb_hooks/main.pb.js
onRecordBeforeCreateRequest((e) => {
// skip if admin
if (e.httpContext.get("admin")) {
return;
}
e.record.set("verified", true)
}, "users")
```
...
It depends on the result of the linked OAuth2 provider response.
In order an existing user to be considered `verified` after OAuth2 auth they need to satisfy one of the conditions:
- the record doesn't have an email
- the email of the record must match with the OAuth2 user email (if returned)

